Gunmen suspected to be kidnappers have abducted one 18-year-old, Victor Egbon, at Zone A, Anguwan Gade Extension of Kuje Area Council of Abuja. Victor is the son of the Proprietor of the Supreme Kids Academy. His father, Abdulsalam Ozigi, who was seriously injured with a deep cut on his body, according to a neighbor was immediately rushed to an undisclosed hospital. Read Also: Vehicles, building razed as gunmen attack Anambra broadcast station   UPDATED: Court to hear Okorocha’s bail application…     Full list of prominent politicians whose children secured…     BREAKING: APC commences screening of presidential aspirants   An eyewitness, who pleaded anonymity, said the bandits stormed the community around 12: 15 am on Monday and invaded the residence of the Ozigis, gained entrance into the house and abducted Victor to an unknown destination. The resident said the kidnappers forcefully destroyed the doors and went into the room and whisked away Victor at gunpoint. Findings revealed that the gunmen were about four in number. All efforts to get the reaction of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Josephine Adeh were futile as she did not respond to calls. The community has been thrown into confusion since the incident occurred.